      "writtenOn": "2020-06-25T05:26:12Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e What are the implications of this change?\nBackground: https://bugs.chromium.org/p/chromium/issues/detail?id\u003d1090671#c22.\n\nCurrently ResultDB cannot differentiate results of a test runs on different gpus - either test_id nor variants has the gpu information.\n\nThis change is to fix that issue.\n\n\u003e \n\u003e - As we test out certain new driver versions, we want to know if they\u0027ve induced flakiness compared to the previous one.\n\u003e - There are different variants of some GPUs on the waterfall (for example, 2 kinds of AMD GPUs on macOS, one very old, one new) and we need to be able to distinguish between the two.\n\nSo I think you agreed to use the gpu tag (the value will be something like \"8086:0102-18.3.6\") as it is, right?",
      "parentUuid": "49bddd82_a1fd559e",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 173,
        "startChar": 32,
        "endLine": 173,
        "endChar": 33
      },
      "revId": "5dbe2ec78c7afaf6145cbb548602ab411e3838b7",
